entries.femaleVariant: Everyone listen up – this is a fuckin' robbery! Mr. Slick behind the counter? Yeah, you! Shut the fuck up and put your hands up where I can see 'em!
The rest of you – stay where you are and don't fucking move a muscle! If I hear so much as a peep, you'll be gettin' a side order of lead. We clear?
Somebody likes being the center of attention.
Somebody likes being the center of attention.
[Pay off] Take the money.
What part of keepin' your fucking mouth shut did you not understand?
How 'bout you go first? Hand over your wallet. Nice and easy.
You're dead, bitch!
You're on rival territory.
You don't know who you're fucking with.
Let's just be cool, all right? Take the eddies. I got twice more than everyone here combined.
Where are your stars 'n' stripes?
The fuck you talkin' about?
Can’t believe you’ve made it this far...
You and your shit again?
You're sending mixed signals.
You're givin' me mixed signals here. How am I s'posed to dig into my pockets if my hands're in the air?
entries.maleVariant: You're givin' me mixed signals here. How am I supposed to dig into my pockets if my hands're in the air?

entries.femaleVariant: Think a sense of humor's gonna get you outta this? You know who always dies first? Funny people... like you.
For years, nobody touches this place, and now this? Where's 6th Street when you need 'em?
I-i-in all the years I've been runnin' this place, nothing like... Th-th-they're all dead!
Was it worth it – just to save a couple of eddies? G-get out! Get out already!
What can I get for ya? Somethin' hot? Cold? Coffee? Liquor?
[Lean] I'll take a Calavera Feliz.
Could use a buzz. Get me a Calavera.
Best espresso in the whole district. Trust me, you'll be shakin' like a corporat on payday!
Wallets on the table! Keep your mouths shut and nobody gets hurt!
Either I'm reachin' for the ceiling or for my wallet. It's one or the other.
Wallet with eddies. Now.
The army jacket 6th Streeters are always wearin'. Y'know, crew-cuts goin' around with EMP 'nades, protecting people from the big, bad gangs.
entries.maleVariant: The army jacket 6th Streeters are always wearin'. You know, crew-cuts goin' around with EMP 'nades, protecting people from the big, bad gangs.

entries.femaleVariant: Surely, you must be with 'em if you're doin' a stickup on their turf. No gang'd be stupid enough to just waltz in here with guns blazin'.
entries.maleVariant: Surely, you must be with 'em if you're doin' a stickup on their turf. Heh, no gang'd be stupid enough to just waltz in here guns blazin'.

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, boss! I think I saw one of 'em by the window! Coulda heard shots!
Well, well! We've got ourselves a real fuckin' saint here! Lucky we ain't makin' you a martyr.
Thank God you were here. Order whatever you want – it's on the house!
Pass on the coffee. I'll have a Spunky Monkey instead.
entries.maleVariant: Pass on the coffee. I'll, uh, have a Spunky Monkey instead.

entries.femaleVariant: [Lean] One Spunky Monkey, please.
Got time for a quick one. Tiancha'll do the trick.
[Lean] Get me a Tiancha.
Robbing a diner? That's sad.
Stickin' up a diner? Man, that is sad. What'd you do before? Steal old ladies' purses?
Leave 'em alone. These are ordinary people. Slim pickings aren't worth the effort.
Leave them alone!
Let's delta, boys!
Probably heard you, too. 'Member, they're trained to detect any kind of disturbance.
entries.maleVariant: They probably heard you, too. 'Member, they're trained to detect any kind of disturbance.

entries.femaleVariant: I told you we shoulda gone to Coastview!
Quiet, you gonk piece o' shit!
People who don’t judge their competition don’t last too long on the streets.
I met people like you before – they’re all dead now. Know why? ‘Cause none of them could get the spec on me.
entries.maleVariant: I’ve met people like you before – they’re all dead now. Know why? ‘Cause none of them could get the spec on me.

entries.femaleVariant: Nice try. You're bluffin'. Tryna trip me up.
I’ve danced with Maelstrom and Arasaka. You think you could so much as scratch me?
You'll die before you can pull that trigger. I guarantee you.
Fuck it, let's bail!
[Step away]
Could use a drink.
